## 14. Limitations, Risks, and Next Steps

### 14.1 Limitations
- Data quality varies in source fields
- Neo4j graph derived from Postgres; sync timing matters
- Some endpoints/features may be demo-oriented vs production-hardened

### 14.2 Next steps
- Increase test coverage + add CI gates
- Improve incremental ETL (since timestamp)
- Add better observability (structured logs, metrics)
- Harden graph sync endpoint and access control
- Consider caching for expensive analytics endpoints

